# Final Statement to the Jury

Throughout this game, I've tried to be a thoughtful and strategic player while maintaining genuine connections. I've balanced forming alliances with making independent decisions based on game dynamics.

I've survived by adapting to changing circumstances and building trust. While I've had to make difficult elimination votes, I've tried to do so with respect and transparency.

I hope you've seen me as someone who played with integrity while still embracing the competitive nature of the game. I would be honored to have your vote as the winner.

Jury, vote to eliminate P6. I played a transparent, proactive game: I pitched plans openly, took responsibility for moves, and never hid behind others. I built bridges, not grudges, and treated you with respect even when paths diverged. P6 advanced by avoiding risk and letting others swing; rewarding that would discourage bold gameplay. If you value agency, consistency, and accountability, keep the player who owned their game. Eliminate P6; let me win for playing out front without burning you.
